<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36196e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36196e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36196e"> 196(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> onion patches</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">So far from abandoning the country, those varlets <font color="green">[Yankee settlers]</font> continued their encroachments, squatting along the great banks of the Varsche river, and founding Hartford, Stamford, New Haven, and other border towns. I have already shown how <mark>the onion patches</mark> of Pyquag were an eyesore to Jacobus Van Curtlet and his garrison, but now these moss-troopers increased in their atrocities, kidnapping hogs, impounding horses, and sometimes grievously rib-roasting their owners. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 149</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
